qas.question: When did Humphrey Gilbert first set sail for the West Indies?
When was Humphrey Gilbert's second attempt to set sail?
What was Humphrey Gilbert's second destination?
What colony did Walter Raleigh found?

context: In <a0_0>1578<a0_0/>, Elizabeth I granted a patent to Humphrey Gilbert for discovery and overseas exploration. That year, Gilbert sailed for the West Indies with the intention of engaging in piracy and establishing a colony in North America, but the expedition was aborted before it had crossed the Atlantic. In <a1_0>1583<a1_0/> he embarked on a second attempt, on this occasion to the island of <a2_0>Newfoundland<a2_0/> whose harbour he formally claimed for England, although no settlers were left behind. Gilbert did not survive the return journey to England, and was succeeded by his half-brother, <a3_0>Walter Raleigh<a3_0/>, who was granted his own patent by Elizabeth in 1584. Later that year, Raleigh founded the colony of <a4_0>Roanoke<a4_0/> on the coast of present-day North Carolina, but lack of supplies caused the colony to fail.
